    • Method Detail

      • setGrid

        public void setGrid(boolean hardmode)
        This method sets up the grid. First places the empRoom and docRoom by treating grid as a 3X3 square and places a room in the center of each square. Each room has a 3 in 10 chance to get the docRoom. The method then calls placeNinja() and placePower(boolean). finally placing player and calling method placePower(boolean).
        Parameters:
        hardmode -

      • placeEmptySpace

        private void placeEmptySpace()
        This method fills grid that still has a null with emptySpace.

      • placeNinja

        private void placeNinja()
        This method places ninja in grid. ninja are placed randomly in grid that is emptySpace. ninja are not placed in safe zone, 3X3 area, near player spawn. Number of starting ninja are assigned to Grid.

      • placePower

        private void placePower(boolean hardmode)
        Places power ups in grid. invuln, addBullet, and radar place on the grid. Only one power up of each type is placed on the board. Power up is only placed in free space emptySpace in the grid.

      • setCover

        public void setCover()
        This method is used to cover the contents of the grid from the player.

      • getGridEntity

        public java.lang.String getGridEntity(int x,
                             int y)
        This method returns the name of the Entity at a specified location. Coordinates given are check to see if they are in grid. If coordinates are out of bounds then function returns a "X".
        Parameters:
        x - Is the X coordinate of the Entity
        y - Is the Y coordinate of the Entity
        Returns:
        Is the name of the Entity.
